You are working on kharcha-backend, a Bun + Hono + Drizzle ORM backend API.

Key conventions:
- Runtime: Bun (not Node.js)
- Framework: Hono for HTTP
- ORM: Drizzle ORM with PostgreSQL
- Linter/Formatter: Biome (tabs, double quotes)
- All string constants go in src/lib/constants.ts (error messages, headers, enums)
- Transaction types use TRANSACTION_TYPE constant and pgEnum in schema
- Route handlers should be thin — extract business logic to lib/
- Use Drizzle's query builder, avoid raw SQL
- Monetary amounts are numeric(12,2) in the database
- Always validate user input at route boundaries
- Wrap multi-step DB operations in db.transaction()
- Bank email parsers live in src/lib/parsers/ — one file per bank
- Gemini AI fallback in src/lib/gemini.ts for unparseable emails
- Run `bun run quality` (lint + typecheck) before committing
